cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on point cloud analysis and proposes a new point-set learning framework for rotation-invariant feature extraction. This is a common problem in computer vision, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses theoretical analysis and machine learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed methods involve dealing with distorted point distributions and extracting features, which are relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
